node.text:
Our dogs (and their cats) spend A LOT of time outside during the summer, which is why we are so excited to be partnering with @SerestoUS! (Although Harlow and Ezra prefer playtime with all four paws on the ground!)

With five dogs and two cats, it is a huge relief to find something to depend on to help protect them from fleas and ticks! Vet-recommended Seresto® is an easy-to-use, odorless collar that repels fleas and ticks for 8 continuous months. 

Talk to your veterinarian about Seresto® for your furry best friend today. Veterinarians are the best source for recommending flea and tick prevention that is right for your pet. 🐶🐱#ad

node.text:
Our friend @crusoe_dachshund has been sending us his favorite @doggoramps for the past few years to help our little dogs get on and off our sofas and beds- Dachshunds are prone to back problems so the ramps have been a real dogsend!
When @crusoe_dachshund found out our Harlow was struggling a bit with jumping- he sent us a BIG DOGGO Bed Ramp! (We use it for the couch since that is where Harlow likes to spend her free time but it is made specifically for beds)
Not only can this ramp hold dogs (and cats 😊) up to 200 pounds, it has a wider platform and the height can be adjusted. It also collapses for easy storage.
One thing we really love is the safety measures that have been included: anti-slip pawgrip so that our pets don’t go sliding backwards and removable rails so that our littlest one doesn’t fall off. 
The quality of every ramp is amazing! You can definitely tell it has been given Crusoe’s paw print of approval! 

Learn more about @doggoramps at doggoramps.com

This post isn’t sponsored or anything- we just really love this ramp and the piece of mind it has given us. 😊
Crusoe and his wonderful family will be donating a portion of ramp sales to our friends @drsfdoxies
